Seismologists said their records showed a death toll of at least 30000. Government officials said many offers of assistance had come from abroad, but no decision had been made about whether to accept them. Patna is the capital of Bihar state, the worst hit area in India. Sunday's quake was felt in the capital, but no deaths or serious damage were reported in the city. The quake injured at least 2000 people in India and 1000 in Nepal, officials said. 5 on the Richter scale and claimed at least 497 lives in Nepal and 200 in India, government officials said. 